The loop invariants must be true before the first iteration of the loop and must still be true after the last iteration.

Based on the loop body and the loop condition, we can identify the following loop invariants:

1. `x1 > 0 && x2 > 0 && x3 > 0`: This invariant is true before the loop starts and must still be true after the loop terminates.
2. `c1 || c2`: This invariant is true before the loop starts and must still be true after the loop terminates.
3. `d1 > 0 && d2 > 0 && d3 > 0`: This invariant is true before the loop starts and must still be true after the loop terminates.

Therefore, the loop invariants for the loop in the given C program are:
```scss
/*@
    loop invariant x1 > 0 && x2 > 0 && x3 > 0;
    loop invariant c1 || c2;
